article.description:
Despite trailing for nearly the entire game, the
Houston Comets escaped with a 71-69 victory over the Minnesota Lynx
on Tuesday night on Janeth Arcain's fade-away jumper with 2 seconds
to play.
article.headline: Smith, Swoopes pass WNBA milestone
article.linkText: Smith, Swoopes pass milestone as Comets outlast Lynx
article.story:
HOUSTON (AP) -- Despite trailing for nearly the entire game, the
Houston Comets escaped with a 71-69 victory over the Minnesota Lynx
on Tuesday night on Janeth Arcain's fade-away jumper with 2 seconds
to play.

Sheryl Swoopes' three-point play with 36 seconds left brought
Houston into a 69-69 tie. The Comets had the chance at the
game-winner after Teresa Edwards missed a 3-pointer on Minnesota's
next possession.

After a timeout, Arcain took the inbounds pass from Tina
Thompson and hit the jumper from just inside the top of the key.

"I am just glad I had the opportunity to win the game for us
after missing some shots earlier," said Arcain, who finished with
13 points on 7-for-12 shooting. "I was glad I made it and kept us
from having to go to overtime."

Swoopes, who led the Comets with 19 points, became the sixth
WNBA player to score 2,500 points when she made her first of two
free throws 7:33 into the second half.

"When it happened, I wasn't even aware that I had gotten
there," said Swoopes who joins teammates Thompson and Cynthia
Cooper at that mark.

"I think it's a great honor whether you win or lose, but when
you can walk away with a win, and win the way we did, obviously it
makes it that much more special," Swoopes said.

Katie Smith of Minnesota then became the seventh player to reach
the milestone when she made two free throws with 2:01 to play. She
finished with 21 points and eight rebounds.

"I had no idea I had that many (points)," Smith said. "The
points don't really matter. It was a tough loss, and they got it at
the buzzer."

Swoopes was scoreless in the first half as the Comets fell
behind by as many as 14 points.

The Lynx used a 20-3 run to take a 22-8 lead. Smith, who was
5-of-6 from the field in the first half, scored seven points during
the run and Sheri Sam added six.

The Comets went on a 14-7 run to close within 29-22 with 5:22
left in the half, but Sam scored four points in the last five
minutes as the Lynx took a 39-29 halftime lead.
